{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"baking tray (30 x 40 cm), baking paper, bottle, rolling pin, oven","id":"r99056","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-O0AsXSAQ7OM\/XZWpuzhw6KI\/AAAAAAAAfOM\/IJiCqX2BbGY9ySxTzU18UEwe9WjzNHbJgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_4XTKIP9jWMRyYSMI.png","title":"Almond tuiles","publishedAt":"2015-08-24T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"content":"35 g unsalted butter"},{"content":"100 g caster sugar"},{"content":"50 g plain flour"},{"content":"2 egg whites"},{"content":"1 pinch sea salt"},{"content":"80 g flaked almonds"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"1.861 g","fat":"4.633 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"8.759 g","calories":"349 kJ \/ 83 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Preheat oven to 180°C. Line a large baking tray (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside."},{"content":"Place butter into mixing bowl and melt <b>2 min\/70°C\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Add sugar, flour, egg whites and salt and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer mixture into a bowl."},{"content":"Place 1½ teaspoons of the mixture onto the prepared baking tray. Using the back of the teaspoon, spread the mixture out into a long oval shape (approx. 8 cm), leaving a 5 cm space between each to allow for spreading during baking."},{"content":"Sprinkle each tuile with flaked almonds and bake for 6-7 minutes (180°C) or until the edge of the biscuits are lightly browned."},{"content":"Remove tuiles from the oven and immediately shape by carefully wrapping each biscuit onto a rolling pin or bottle. Leave to cool before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Once cooled store tuiles in a sealable container as they will soften quickly.","Stencil 8 cm oval shapes onto the baking paper to help as a guide for spreading out the mixture."],"basicInfo":["medium","15m","30m","16 portions"]}